                            "body": {
                                "type": "TextualBody",
                                "format": "text/html",
                                "value": "<p>Depiction of a gilded altarpiece with Saint Paul (left, in red) and Saint Peter (right, in blue) holding representations of liturgical texts.</p>"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "https://ciiipreses.github.io/sanisidoro/iiif/bfhdok-affesc4mgnhlbi/canvas/1/annopage-2/anno-2",
                            "type": "Annotation",
                            "motivation": "commenting",
                            "target": "https://ciiipreses.github.io/sanisidoro/iiif/bfhdok-affesc4mgnhlbi/canvas/1#xywh=1549,952,544,318",
                            "body": {
                                "type": "TextualBody",
                                "format": "text/html",
                                "value": "<p>Metapictorial choir book with musical notation for the chant <em>Terribilis est locus iste</em> (Cantus ID <a href=\"https://cantusindex.org/id/007763\">007763</a>) at right, corresponding to the original liturgical context for this historiated initial&nbsp;‘T’.</p>"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "https://ciiipreses.github.io/sanisidoro/iiif/bfhdok-affesc4mgnhlbi/canvas/1/annopage-2/anno-3",
                            "type": "Annotation",
                            "motivation": "commenting",
                            "target": "https://ciiipreses.github.io/sanisidoro/iiif/bfhdok-affesc4mgnhlbi/canvas/1#xywh=1535,1294,653,809",
                            "body": {
                                "type": "TextualBody",
                                "format": "text/html",
                                "value": "<p>A brown-robed Observant Jeronymite friar prays over an altar covered with a white cloth. Founded by Lope de Olmedo (<a href=\"https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q55835391\">Q55835391</a>), the Observant Jeronymites were centered at the monastery of San Isidoro del Campo (<a href=\"https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q778571\">Q778571</a>) in Santiponce, near Seville, and existed as an independent branch of the Order of Saint Jerome (<a href=\"https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q1474312\">Q1474312</a>).</p>"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                }
